Deputies proposed to speed up the entry into force of the law on personal data
In case of success of the initiative, these Russians will not be stored on servers abroad from 1 January 2015
In the state Duma a draft law providing for the postponement of the date of entry into force of the law on personal data of Russians - from 1 September 2016 to 1 January 2015.
Initiative is available in the database of the legislative activity of the lower chamber.
Was sponsored by the deputies of the state Duma Vadim Dengin, Yaroslav Nilov (LDPR), Evgeny Fedorov ("United Russia"), Vladimir Parakhin ("Fair Russia") and Alexander Yushchenko (CPRF).
This change, according to the authors of the initiative, will contribute to more rapid and effective enforcement of rights of citizens of the Russian Federation on the safety of personal data and the secrecy of correspondence and telecommunications networks.
The law, the entry into force of which hasten parliamentarians obliged to keep on the territory of the Russian Federation the personal data of Russian citizens, processed via the Internet.
He also makes a must-have recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, updating and retrieval of personal data of Russian citizens in databases located on the territory of Russia, and indication information about the location of such databases.
In addition, the act gives Roskomnadzor law on the basis of a court decision to restrict access to information processed in violation of the legislation of the Russian Federation in the field of personal data.
The law also proposes the creation of so-called "black lists" of illegal sites - automated information system "Register of infringers of rights of personal data subjects".
This law was passed by the Parliament in the summer.
The authors of the bill were made by Andrei Lugovoi and Vadim Dengin from LDPR Alexander Yushchenko from the Communist party.
The dengin and Yushchenko is also one of the authors of the current bill to change the date of entry into force of the law.
For those who have data centers in the Russian Federation there is no need to pay rent
Commenting on submitted today to the state Duma a bill, the first Deputy head of the Duma Committee on information policy, Leonid Levin stated that he sees no problems for the postponement of the date of entry into force of the law on personal data protection.
According to him, those companies that, by 1 January 2015 will not have their own repositories of personal data of Russian citizens on the territory of the Russian Federation, will be able to rent them, for example, "from "Rostelecom", which have repeatedly said that they are ready to provide your servers to rent and already provides its servers, Mail Group, Western companies, which today provide their servers.
"Besides, there are several independent data centers, is ready to cooperate in this area", he added.
"If companies decide to comply with the law and continue to work in Russia, I do not see problems - they have the technological capabilities to host," concluded Levin.
A controversial bill
Immediately after the publication of the draft law of the Russian Association of electronic communications expressed concern that if the bill is passed, the Russians will no longer be able to use many global Internet services.
In particular, we are talking about the online booking services of air tickets and hotels.
According to the Association, "the bill deprives the subjects of personal data of citizens of the Russian Federation right to manage their own data peremptory determining that their entry, filing, etc. should be provided only in databases located on the territory of the Russian Federation".
In a statement RAEC emphasizes that a more effective measure would be the establishment of a mechanism to inform the user about where the recording, systematization of personal data.
In this case, he will be able to choose which site will be the steps.
The adoption of such bills on the "localization" of personal data in other countries has led to global care services, and significant economic losses.
