The Ministry of communications has proposed to allocate 250 million rubles broadcasting company "Crimea"
The Ministry of communications has proposed to allocate in 2014 from the Federal budget of 250 million rubles of the Autonomous nonprofit organization "TV and radio company "Crimea".
This is stated in the draft decree prepared by the Ministry, which read "Tape.<url>".
According to the explanatory note to the draft, subsidies from the Federal budget will be directed on a covering of expenses on creation of conditions for large-scale media coverage of the socio-economic situation and development of modern information space on the territory of the Republic of Crimea, including the purchase of equipment".
In particular, the allocated money is supposed to convert the Studio unit, video walls, Central hardware and videoserver.
It is also planned acquisition of mobile television stations and a satellite transmitter.
In addition, from the allocated funds, the company will pay for the use of fiber-optic communication lines (FOCL) and repair of the system energy.
Subsidies will be provided within the means of the Federal budget provided to the Ministry of communications.
State broadcasting company "Crimea" established in 1959, broadcasting in seven languages: Ukrainian, Russian, Crimean Tatar, German, Greek, Bulgarian and Armenian.
To date coverage of television signal broadcasting company is more than 75 percent of the Peninsula.
In 2011, "TV and radio company "Crimea" has received a license for television broadcasting in digital format.
